ERROR HANDLING / EXCEPTION HANDLING :- 
   ======================================

   1 syntax errors
   2 logical errors 
   3 runtime errors

 => errors that are raised during program execution are called runtime errors 
 
  ex :-     DECLARE
                   a  NUMBER(3) ;
             BEGIN
                  a := &a;         => 1000    => runtime error
                DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE(a);
             END;
               / 
    
   => if stmt causes runtime error then execution is terminated abnormally and oracle displays
        error message , To end the program normally and to replace oracle error message with
        our own simple and user friendly message then we need to handle that runtime error.

  => To handle runtime error then include a block called  EXCEPTION block

       DECLARE
             declaration-part;
        BEGIN
             execution-part;        => stmts causes exception
        EXCEPTION
             error handling -part   => stmt handles exception
        END;
           /
 
 => exceptions are 2 types 

 1  system defined 
 2  user defined 

